message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed taxonomy and algorithm also involve machine learning techniques such as decision trees and random forests, which fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with predicting the reasons for answer differences in visual question answering.
